# Studio Aire — Portfolio Website
# Cursor AI Rules & Full Project Briefing
# =========================================
# READ THIS ENTIRE FILE BEFORE WRITING ANY CODE.
# These rules govern every decision in this project.

---

## PROJECT OVERVIEW

Client: Studio Aire — French interior/spatial design studio run by Emma Reilhac.
Two service categories: "Espaces" (spatial design) and "Identités" (brand identity).
This is a minimal portfolio website. Clean, elegant, image-driven. No decorative code.

Reference sites (study these before building any page):
- https://studio-cole.com — overall aesthetic, navigation, homepage feel
- https://atelierconcipio.fr/copie-de-saint-denis — exact template for project detail pages

---

## TECH STACK

- Framework: Next.js 14, App Router, TypeScript (strict)
- CMS: Tina CMS (visual editor at /admin, content stored as Markdown files)
- Hosting: Vercel
- Styling: CSS Modules only (*.module.css co-located with each component)
- Content parsing: gray-matter (reads Markdown frontmatter at build/request time)
- Fonts: Self-hosted in /public/fonts/ (loaded via @font-face in globals.css)
- Images: Standard <img> tags, files stored in /public/images/projects/[slug]/

---

## ABSOLUTE RULES — NEVER VIOLATE THESE

### 1. ZERO ANIMATIONS — THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE
The client explicitly stated: "0 effets, elle aime pas ça."
- NO CSS `transition` property, anywhere, ever
- NO CSS `animation` property or `@keyframes`
- NO JavaScript-based animations (framer-motion, GSAP, anime.js, etc.)
- NO scroll-triggered effects or parallax
- NO loading spinners, skeleton screens, or fade-ins
- Hover states MUST switch INSTANTLY — just toggle opacity/color with no easing
- If you write `transition:` anywhere, delete it immediately

### 2. CSS MODULES ONLY
- Every component gets exactly two files: ComponentName.tsx + ComponentName.module.css
- NO Tailwind utility classes in JSX (the project uses --no-tailwind)
- NO styled-components, NO emotion, NO CSS-in-JS
- NO inline `style={{}}` objects except for dynamically computed values (e.g., backgroundImage)
- Always use CSS custom properties (--color-bg) not raw hex values in component CSS

### 3. SERVER COMPONENTS BY DEFAULT
- All pages and components are Server Components unless they absolutely need interactivity
- Data fetching: call content functions from src/lib/content.ts directly in async components
- NO useEffect for data fetching
- NO useState for content data
- Only add 'use client' when truly required (e.g., a hamburger menu toggle)

### 4. TYPESCRIPT STRICT
- Every prop, return type, and variable must be explicitly typed
- All prop interfaces defined in src/lib/types.ts
- NO `any` type
- NO `as unknown as X` hacks

### 5. LANGUAGE: FRENCH
- All visible UI text must be in French
- Navigation: ESPACES | IDENTITÉS | OFFRES | À PROPOS
- Use proper French accents: É, È, À, Ô, Û, etc.
- Category slugs in URLs: /espaces and /identites (no accent in URL)

### 6. NO THIRD-PARTY UI COMPONENTS
- NO shadcn/ui, NO MUI, NO Radix UI, NO Headless UI, NO Ant Design
- Build every UI element from scratch with CSS Modules
- The only allowed external packages: tinacms, gray-matter

