## CONTENT SCHEMA (Markdown frontmatter)

Spaces and Identities have different fields. Shared fields come first, then category-specific ones.

### Spaces project file:

```yaml
---
title: "Nom du projet"
slug: "nom-du-projet"
year: "2024"
client: "Nom du client"
projectType: "apartment"
location: "Paris — France"
description: "Réhabilitation complète d'un appartement"
surface: "80 m²"
planImage: "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/plan.jpg"
coverImage: "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/cover.jpg"
images:
  - "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/01.jpg"
  - "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/02.jpg"
---
```

### Identities project file:

```yaml
---
title: "Nom du projet"
slug: "nom-du-projet"
year: "2024"
client: "Nom du client"
projectType: "visual identity"
location: "Paris — France"
description: "Création de l'identité visuelle"
mission: "conception/réalisation"
coverImage: "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/cover.jpg"
images:
  - "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/01.jpg"
  - "/images/projects/nom-du-projet/02.jpg"
---
```

- `slug` must be kebab-case, URL-safe, no accents
- `coverImage` is used in grids and carousels
- `images` is the ordered list shown in the right column of the detail page
- `planImage` (Spaces only) is a small plan image shown at the bottom of the sticky left column
- `surface` (Spaces only) e.g. "80 m²"
- `mission` (Identities only) e.g. "conception/réalisation"
- `description` is shown in the meta block of the detail view

